 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "`:finishing-governor` is implemented end-to-end in `src/finishing` as a
 BUILDING-COMPLETION/FINISHING-PROJECT OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor --
 Finishing Advisor (LLM proposal-only) ⊣ Finishing Governor (closed-op-
 allowlist / site-verification / pre-work hazmat-survey / fall-protection
 / unresolved-concern hard-gates). Deliberately narrower in authority than
 the `cloud-itonami-isic-4211` (construction) robotics-premise reference
 this actor follows structurally: `:itonami.blueprint/robotics` is
 honestly `false` here -- this actor holds NO trade-equipment-control
 authority and NO structural-completion-sign-off authority (both are
 HARD, permanent governor blocks, never overridable by human approval --
 see `finishing.governor` ns docstring). Every one of its four proposal
 ops (`:log-site-record` / `:schedule-finishing-operation` / `:flag-
 safety-concern` / `:order-supplies`) carries `:effect :propose` ONLY --
 the governor HARD-holds any proposal that doesn't
 (`effect-not-propose-violations`), a structural invariant distinguishing
 this actor from siblings that DO commit real-world actuation effects.
 Per-jurisdiction pre-work hazmat-survey / fall-protection legal-basis
 catalog (JPN/USA/DEU, `finishing.facts`) with real official sources
 (independently verified against osha.gov / ecfr.gov / laws.e-gov.go.jp /
 eur-lex.europa.eu / baua.de before being written), and mail+phone
 safety-concern notification (`finishing.notify`, a portable `.cljc`
 caller-injected transport seam -- no JVM interop, per this repo's
 cljs-first mandate) to the site's supervisor/safety-officer contact
 roster. `:flag-safety-concern` ALWAYS escalates to a human, at every
 phase, unconditionally. UNLIKE the `cloud-itonami-isic-4311`/`cloud-
 itonami-isic-4210` sibling actors, `:schedule-finishing-operation` here
 is NOT a permanent `high-stakes` member -- it MAY auto-commit at phase 3
 once every HARD check clears and confidence is high, reflecting
 building-completion/finishing trade work's materially lower risk profile
 relative to demolition or heavy-civil earthwork scheduling (see
 `finishing.governor`/`finishing.phase` ns docstrings for the full
 rationale). See `docs/` -- README `Actuation` section -- for the full
 governor-check enumeration and the rationale for each hard/soft rule."}
